        "content": "<div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"Lean4\"><pre><span></span><code><span class=\"kn\">inductive</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">Metacircuit</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"kt\">Type</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:=</span>\n<span class=\"bp\">|</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">Abs</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">String</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">-&gt;</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">Metacircuit</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">-&gt;</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">Metacircuit</span>\n<span class=\"bp\">|</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">App</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">Metacircuit</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">-&gt;</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">Metacircuit</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">-&gt;</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">Metacircuit</span>\n</code></pre></div>\n<p>I don't know how to construct terms of this type</p>",
        "id": 466776596,
        "sender_full_name": "Quinn",
        "timestamp": 1725234234
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>shouldn't the termination checker disallow this?</p>",
        "id": 466776756,
        "sender_full_name": "Quinn",
        "timestamp": 1725234310
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>It's perfectly fine to have a type for which you cannot construct any terms. An example of such a type is <code>False</code>. In fact, you can show that having a term of your type means you can construct one of <code>False</code>:</p>\n<div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"Lean4\"><pre><span></span><code><span class=\"kn\">inductive</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">Metacircuit</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"kt\">Type</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:=</span>\n<span class=\"bp\">|</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">Abs</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">String</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">-&gt;</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">Metacircuit</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">-&gt;</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">Metacircuit</span>\n<span class=\"bp\">|</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">App</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">Metacircuit</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">-&gt;</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">Metacircuit</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">-&gt;</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">Metacircuit</span>\n\n<span class=\"kn\">example</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">Metacircuit</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">â†’</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">False</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"k\">by</span>\n<span class=\"w\">  </span><span class=\"n\">intro</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">m</span>\n<span class=\"w\">  </span><span class=\"n\">induction</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">m</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"k\">with</span>\n<span class=\"w\">  </span><span class=\"bp\">|</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">Abs</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">_</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">_</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">ih</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">=&gt;</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">trivial</span>\n<span class=\"w\">  </span><span class=\"bp\">|</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">App</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">_</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">_</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">=&gt;</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">trivial</span>\n</code></pre></div>",
        "id": 466781045,
        "sender_full_name": "Eric Paul",
        "timestamp": 1725236699
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Oh right.</p>",
        "id": 466785721,
        "sender_full_name": "Quinn",
        "timestamp": 1725239066
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>So there's like a spectrum between failing the termination checker and constructing a proof of false?</p>",
        "id": 466785755,
        "sender_full_name": "Quinn",
        "timestamp": 1725239098
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Why not just get rid of the termination checker, and use malformed types to construct proofs of false?</p>",
        "id": 466785777,
        "sender_full_name": "Quinn",
        "timestamp": 1725239109
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>I had forgotten about constructorless types and how they might relate, so thanks!</p>",
        "id": 466785842,
        "sender_full_name": "Quinn",
        "timestamp": 1725239154
    },
    {
        "content": "<p><span class=\"user-mention silent\" data-user-id=\"693606\">Quinn</span> <a href=\"#narrow/stream/113489-new-members/topic/why.20does.20this.20inductive.20compile.20with.20no.20base.20cases.3F/near/466785777\">said</a>:</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p>Why not just get rid of the termination checker, and use malformed types to construct proofs of false?</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p>I would think that we want to have non-inhabited types. Sometimes it might be interesting and hard to prove whether a type is inhabited.</p>\n<p>Proofs of False should clearly not be allowed. Did I misunderstandil the question?</p>",
        "id": 466800079,
        "sender_full_name": "Adomas Baliuka",
        "timestamp": 1725245323
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Oops! Didn't mean proof of false, meant A-&gt;False</p>",
